gnitude, whereas the apparent luminosity observed from the top of\nthe column is much less. Due to such highly anisotropic radiation fields,\nobserved flux should exhibit periodic variations with the rotation period,\nprovided that the rotation and magnetic axes are misaligned.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Aug 2016 08:58:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 30 Aug 2016 02:13:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-09"}
