 emission (obtained from the density) matches the observed\nlocation of the CME leading edge. From the above evidence we propose that the\nradio sparks are caused by the quasi-periodic fast waves, and the emission is\ngenerated as they catch up and interact with the leading edge of the CME.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Aug 2016 10:57:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-19"}
